==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: internship
<hw>in"tern*ship</hw> <pr>(⟦icr⟧n"t⟦etil⟧rn*sh⟦icr⟧p)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>The state of being an
intern; the position of an intern.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The period of time during which a person is an
intern; <as>as, she served her <ex>internship</ex> over the
summer</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A program to provide novices in a field with
apprenticeship training.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>The period of time during which a novice in a field
serves in a subordinate capacity and continues to gain experience; the
learning period before one becomes an expert.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Internuncial</ent>⟦br⟧
